            <section id="Theft">
                <h2>Theft</h2>
                <p>
                    A theft incident is when someone takes something that doesn't belong to them without asking or without
                    permission. It's like when a person borrows your toy without asking and keeps it for themselves, which
                    is not okay.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <h3>Safety Tips:</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><p><strong>Be aware of your surroundings:</strong> Stay alert and attentive to your environment,
                        especially in crowded places or unfamiliar areas. Avoid distractions such as using your phone excessively
                        or wearing headphones that may compromise your awareness.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Secure your belongings:</strong> Keep your valuable items, such as wallets, purses, and
                        electronics, in a secure place and out of sight. Avoid displaying expensive jewelry or carrying large
                        amounts of cash.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Use locks and security measures:</strong> Utilize locks on your doors and windows at home
                        and in your car. Invest in a sturdy lock for your bike or motorcycle, and use a secure storage area
                        when leaving it unattended.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Avoid leaving items unattended:</strong> Never leave your belongings unattended in public
                        areas, even for a brief moment. Thieves can act quickly, so keep your items within sight or physically
                        secured.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Keep important documents safe:</strong> Store your important documents, such as passports,
                        identification cards, and social security cards, in a secure location at home. When traveling, carry
                        only the necessary identification documents and leave the rest securely stored.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Be cautious with personal information:</strong> Be mindful of who you share personal
                        information with. Avoid providing sensitive details to strangers.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Travel with a companion when possible:</strong> When walking in unfamiliar or potentially
                        unsafe areas, it's advisable to travel with a companion. Thieves are less likely to target a group of
                        people.</p></li>
                    </ul>
                    <h3>Resources:</h3>
