            <section id="Robbery">
                <h2>Robbery</h2>
                <p>
                    A robbery is when someone takes something valuable from another person without their permission and
                    usually uses force or threats to do so. It's important to report a robbery to the police so they can
                    help catch the person responsible and make sure everyone stays safe.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <h3>Safety Tips:</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><p><strong>Be aware of your surroundings:</strong> Stay vigilant and attentive to your
                        environment at all times. Pay attention to people nearby and any suspicious activities or
                        individuals.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Stick to well-lit and populated areas:</strong> Avoid walking alone in dimly lit or
                        secluded areas, especially at night. Stick to busy streets and well-populated areas where there are
                        more potential witnesses.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Avoid displaying wealth:</strong> Avoid flaunting valuable items, such as expensive
                        jewelry, watches, or electronics, as they can attract unwanted attention. Keep these items discreet
                        and out of sight when in public.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Use ATMs and banks with caution:</strong> When using an ATM, choose well-lit and busy
                        locations. Shield your PIN number from prying eyes, and be cautious of anyone suspiciously nearby. If
                        possible, use ATMs located inside banks or establishments.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Maintain home security:</strong> Secure your home with sturdy locks on doors and windows.
                        Install a peephole or a doorbell camera to identify visitors before opening the door. Consider a home
                        security system that includes alarms and surveillance cameras.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Be cautious with social media:</strong> Avoid sharing your whereabouts or detailed
                        personal information on social media platforms. Robbers can potentially gather information from your
                        posts to target your home or track your movements.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Vary your routines:</strong> Robbers often look for predictable patterns. Vary your daily
                        routines, such as the routes you take or the times you leave and return home. This makes it more
                        difficult for someone to anticipate your movements.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Maintain good communication:</strong> Let someone you trust know your whereabouts and
                        schedule, especially if you're going out alone or to unfamiliar areas. Regularly check-in with friends or
                        family members, so they know you are safe.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Consider self-defense training:</strong> Learning basic self-defense techniques can provide
                        you with the skills and confidence to protect yourself if confronted with a dangerous situation. Consider
                        enrolling in a self-defense class or workshop.</p></li>
                    </ul>
                    <h3>Resources:</h3>
