                <section id="Murder">
                <h2>Murder</h2>
                <p>
                    A murder is when someone intentionally hurts another person so badly that they die. It is a very
                    serious crime, and the police need to be told about it so they can investigate and make sure the
                    person who did it is caught and punished.
                </p>
                    <ul>
                    <h3>Safety Tips:</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><p><strong>Be aware of your surroundings:</strong> Stay attentive to your environment and the people
                        around you. Avoid walking alone in isolated or dangerous areas, especially at night.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Secure your home:</strong> Ensure your home has proper security measures in place, including
                        sturdy locks on doors and windows. Consider installing a security system, including surveillance cameras
                        and alarms.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Practice online safety:</strong> Be cautious about sharing personal information online and be
                         mindful of your social media presence. Avoid disclosing sensitive details that could potentially make you a
                         target.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Avoid conflicts and aggression:</strong> Whenever possible, try to defuse conflicts peacefully
                        and walk awayfrom potentially volatile situations. Avoid engaging in confrontations or escalating arguments.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Stay connected in public:</strong> </p>When in public places, such as malls or parks, try to stay with
                        a group or near other people. Criminals are less likely to target individuals who are surrounded by others.</li>
                        <li><p><strong>Plan safe transportation:</strong> When using public transportation or ridesharing services, make sure
                        to verify the identity of the driver and the vehicle before getting in. Share your travel plans with someone you trust.</p></li>
                    </ul>
                    <h3>Resources:</h3>
                    <ul>
