            <section id="Rape">
                <h2>Rape</h2>
                <p>
                    A rape incident is a very serious and harmful act when someone hurts another person in a very
                    wrong way without their permission. It's important to tell a trusted adult if you or someone you
                    know experiences this, so they can help and keep everyone safe.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <h3>Safety Tips:</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><p><strong>Be aware of your surroundings:</strong> Stay attentive and aware of your environment,
                        especially in unfamiliar or isolated areas. Avoid walking alone at night, particularly in dimly lit
                        or secluded places.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Plan your outings:</strong> When going out, let someone you trust know your plans,
                        including where you're going and when you expect to return. Consider traveling with a friend or in a
                        group, particularly to parties, bars, or other social events.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Watch your drink:</strong> Never leave your drink unattended, and be cautious about
                        accepting drinks from strangers. If you set your drink down, get a new one to ensure it hasn't been
                        tampered with.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Be cautious with personal information:</strong> Be mindful of sharing personal details
                        with people you don't know well, both online and offline. Avoid disclosing specific information about
                        your routine, address, or daily activities.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Learn self-defense:</strong> Consider taking self-defense classes to learn techniques
                        that can help you protect yourself in dangerous situations. Knowing how to physically defend yourself
                        can boost your confidence and potentially deter attackers.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Use well-lit and populated areas:</strong> Stick to well-lit and busy streets when walking,
                        particularly at night. Avoid shortcuts through dark or deserted areas where you may be more vulnerable.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Trustworthy transportation:</strong> If using a ridesharing service, ensure that the driver and
                        vehicle match the information provided by the app. Travel in the back seat, and share your trip details with
                        someone you trust.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Stay sober:</strong> Consuming alcohol or drugs can impair your judgment and make you more
                        vulnerable to potential perpetrators. Be mindful of your alcohol consumption and never leave your drink
                        unattended.</p></li>
                    </ul>
