            <section id="Drug_Trafficking">
                <h2>Drug Trafficking</h2>
                <p>
                    The illegal transportation, distribution, and sale of controlled substances, often involving
                    organized criminal networks and smuggling across borders.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <h3>How to recognize:</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><p><strong>Unusual behavior or activities:</strong> Look for individuals exhibiting suspicious
                        behavior, such as frequent and brief visits to specific locations, unusual patterns of movement, or
                        interactions with multiple individuals involved in criminal activities.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Excessive cash transactions:</strong> Drug traffickers often deal in large sums of
                        cash to avoid traceability. Be cautious of individuals making frequent cash transactions, especially
                        if they involve significant amounts of money or are conducted in a secretive or suspicious manner.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Unmarked or inconspicuous vehicles:</strong> Watch for vehicles with modified features,
                        such as hidden compartments, darkened windows, or altered license plates. These modifications can be used to
                        transport drugs discreetly.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>High-security measures:</strong>  Drug traffickers may employ heightened security measures to
                        protect their operations. This can include surveillance cameras, guards, or restricted access to certain
                        areas. Be observant of properties or locations with excessive security measures that seem disproportionate
                        to their legitimate activities.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Suspicious packaging or cargo:</strong> Be alert to packages, parcels, or cargo that appear
                        suspicious, irregularly shaped, or exhibit unusual weight or odor. Drug traffickers may use innovative
                        methods to conceal drugs within legitimate shipments.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Increased foot traffic or short-term visitors:</strong> Pay attention to locations where
                        there is an unusually high volume of people coming and going, especially if they stay for only brief periods.
                        Drug trafficking operations may involve frequent visits from buyers, suppliers, or intermediaries.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Chemical odors or strange smells:</strong> Certain drugs have distinctive odors. Be attentive
                        to strong chemical or pungent smells emanating from specific areas or properties, as they may indicate drug
                        production or storage.</p></li>
                    </ul>
                    <h3>Resources:</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><a href="https://pdea.gov.ph/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&layout=edit&id=69"><p>Philippine Drug Enforcement Agency (PDEA)</p></a></li>
                    </ul>
                </ul>
