            <section id="Lost_and_Found">
                <h2>Lost and Found</h2>
                <p>
                    Lost and Found incidents involve the misplacement or discovery of personal belongings or
                    valuable items, requiring individuals to report or locate their lost possessions.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <h3>How to avoid:</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><p><strong>Organize your belongings:</strong> Keep your belongings organized and have designated places for
                        frequently used items such as keys, wallet, phone, and other essentials. Consistently returning items to their
                        designated spots can help prevent misplacement.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Use a secure bag or wallet:</strong> Choose a bag or wallet with secure closures, such as zippers
                        or clasps, to prevent items from falling out accidentally. Make sure it has compartments or pockets to keep items
                        organized and easily accessible.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Be mindful of your belongings:</strong> Stay aware and conscious of your belongings when you're
                        outside. Avoid placing items on unstable surfaces or in places where they can easily be forgotten or left
                        behind.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Minimize distractions:</strong> When you're engrossed in conversations, using your phone, or
                        engaging in other activities, it's easy to lose track of your belongings. Try to minimize distractions and make
                        a conscious effort to keep an eye on your items.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Avoid overloading yourself:</strong> Carrying too many items at once can increase the chances of
                        dropping or misplacing something. Be mindful of your capacity and avoid carrying more than you can comfortably
                        manage.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Utilize pockets or small bags:</strong> Consider using pockets or small bags specifically
                        designed to hold essential items like keys, cards, or small electronics. These can help keep important items
                        separate and easily accessible.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Attach important items to a keychain or lanyard:</strong> For items like keys or access cards,
                        consider attaching them to a keychain or lanyard that you can securely carry or wear around your neck. This makes
                        it less likely for them to be misplaced or dropped accidentally.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Double-check before leaving:</strong> Before leaving a location, take a moment to do a quick check
                        to ensure you haven't left any belongings behind. Look around the area where you were seated or standing, and make
                        sure you have everything you brought with you.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Keep a checklist:</strong> If you have multiple items to carry, consider maintaining a checklist of
                        the essential items you need to have with you. Before leaving a location, refer to the checklist to ensure you have
                        all your belongings.</p></li>
                        <li><p><strong>Use technology:</strong> Consider utilizing technology to help you keep track of your belongings.
                        For example, you can use smartphone apps or Bluetooth-enabled trackers to locate items if they go missing or help
                        you remember where you last had them.</p></li>
                    </ul>
